  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\nUser A sends `~first text~ *second text*` to any chat\r\nAs result, only `first text` is shown for both users \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n~first text~ *second text* - is shown for User A and User B\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nfirst text  - is shown for User A and User B\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status on 2 devices \r\n- As  User A start new chat with User B\r\n- As User A enter `~first text~ *second text*` into message input\r\n- Tap on 'Send message' button\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version:  <img width=\"137\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-03-15 at 8 13 25 am\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12611990/37447057-cd135b0c-2828-11e8-8dea-ff5d65a07b39.png\">\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS",
